============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is quantum mechanics?
A1: Quantum mechanics describes physics at atomic and
     subatomic scales. Key principles: wave-particle
     duality, uncertainty principle, superposition, and
     quantum entanglement.

Q2: What is the Renaissance?
A2: The Renaissance (14th-17th century) was a cultural
     rebirth in Europe featuring renewed interest in Greco-
     Roman art, humanism, and early science. Began in Italy;
     spread across Europe.

Q3: What is a neuron?
A3: A neuron is a nerve cell that processes and transmits
     information through electrical and chemical signals.
     Key parts: dendrites (receive signals), cell body, axon
     (send signals).

Q4: What is an algorithm?
A4: An algorithm is a step-by-step procedure for solving a
     problem. Algorithms have inputs, defined steps, and
     outputs. Examples: sorting, searching, path-finding.

Q5: What is capitalism?
A5: Capitalism is an economic system where private
     individuals own the means of production and markets
     determine prices and production through supply and
     demand.

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Bayes Theorem
Branch:       Probability
Formula:      P(H|E) = P(E|H)P(H)/P(E)
Applications: ML, spam filters, medical testing
Discoverer:   Thomas Bayes (1763)

Theorem/Law:  Pythagorean Theorem
Branch:       Geometry
Formula:      a² + b² = c²
Applications: Navigation, construction, computer graphics
Discoverer:   Pythagoras (500)

Theorem/Law:  Central Limit Theorem
Branch:       Statistics
Formula:      Sample means approach normal distribution
Applications: Polling, quality control, finance
Discoverer:   Lyapunov (1901)

