Invention:  Radio
Year:       1895
Inventor:   Guglielmo Marconi
Country:    Italy
Category:   Communication
Description:Wireless electromagnetic transmission
Impact:     Enabled broadcasting; news, entertainment, military

Invention:  Telegraph
Year:       1837
Inventor:   Samuel Morse
Country:    USA
Category:   Communication
Description:Electrical coded message transmission
Impact:     First rapid long-distance communication

Invention:  mRNA Vaccine
Year:       2020
Inventor:   BioNTech/Moderna
Country:    Germany/USA
Category:   Medicine
Description:mRNA instructs cells to produce antigen
Impact:     COVID vaccines; platform for cancer, flu, HIV vaccines

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Rationalism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   Some knowledge is innate or derivable by reason alone
Philosopher:  Descartes/Spinoza
Example:      Math truths like 2+2=4 are known by reason, not experiment

Concept:      Nihilism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Life has no inherent meaning; values are human inventions
Philosopher:  Nietzsche (diagnosed)
Example:      Without objective grounding, all moral frameworks are invented

Concept:      Utilitarianism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Maximize pleasure minimize pain across all sentient beings
Philosopher:  Jeremy Bentham
Example:      Felicific calculus: measure units of pleasure and pain

